<br>
-No class should walk into pop with 100 aa, and about a month later have 340 (yes an enchanter on sz did this). It trivializes the game and experience.<br>
<br>
-<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>No class</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> should have access to an ability which trivializes so many roles (damage dealing and tanking) to the point where you can exp <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>better</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> than a group <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>and</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> do it with the assistance of just ONE (1) class. In fact even a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>solo</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> enchanter probably could exp as well as a group.<br>
<br>
-A class which is easily one of the most group friendly should not also solo better than a well put together exp group makes exp.<br>
<br>
Charm breaks <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>every one</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> of those above outlined basic properties of balance, to the point where there is no reason to play any other class besides an enchanter. They have the best damage mitigation (tanking, mezzes, slows, runes, stuns, root, ect), the best supportive abilities (haste and c), and the best damage dealing (380 was the highest furor claims to have logged). Litterally the only thing enchanters cant do is heal, in fact they probably can even do that if they charm a cleric pet, lol. <br>
<br>
Lets be honest with ourselves, you cant say thats working can you? Enchanters are a god class. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fallacy6666>fallacy6666</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#333333>(12/20/02 9:34:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=399.topic&index=65>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   charm</span><hr size=1> charm has been broken ever since they changed the magic resist rate. Before the charm speels were to unreliable and break real quick. Now just about every time they last the whole duration. This is a big blow to all pet classes, especially us! I have seen an enchanter in chardock that charms that level 52 sergent that stands on top of the casle, and completly inelate every lower mob that stands there.<br>
