<br>
The real problem as I see it is that unlike summoned pets, charmed ones do not suffer from the PC power curve flattening that occurs as you move into the upper levels (actually for most of the game this happens). The game is carefully tuned such that as you advance, it is required that you overcome more and more deadly opponents.<br>
<br>
This requires a certain gathering of skill and experience, friends and allies, as compared to mobs every player continues ot lose ground and to continue to advance you have to deal with this.<br>
<br>
Charm's power comes form this very fact. The very fact that you can take a monster that will take a group to dispose of and turn it into a weapon is really the core of the problem.<br>
<br>
No nerfs ... <p><center>
